<div id="review_193643710" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/193643710" />
    <a title="Molly" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/656253-molly"><img alt="Molly" src="https://s.gr-assets.com/assets/nophoto/user/f_50x66-6a03a5c12233c941481992b82eea8d23.png" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/193643710?book_show_action=true">Aug 02, 2011</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Molly" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Molly" href="/user/show/656253-molly">Molly</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer193643710" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer4605020528059026989">Of course, I love &quot;The Actor&apos;s Nightmare&quot; but &quot;Sister Mary Ignatius Explains It All for You&quot; is side splittingly funny. I guess it&apos;s because I am Catholic and because I love black humor. Christopher Durang is edgy and witty so if you&apos;re expecting Neil Simon, you probably want to read something else.</span>
  <span id="freeText4605020528059026989" style="display:none">Of course, I love "The Actor's Nightmare" but "Sister Mary Ignatius Explains It All for You" is side splittingly funny. I guess it's because I am Catholic and because I love black humor. Christopher Durang is edgy and witty so if you're expecting Neil Simon, you probably want to read something else.</span>
  <a data-text-id="4605020528059026989" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


